# Backend API URL
# IMPORTANT: This must be the server's network IP address (not 127.0.0.1).
# When a browser on another PC opens the dashboard, it uses this URL to
# reach the backend. If you put 127.0.0.1 here, other PCs will look for
# the backend on their own machine and fail to connect.
#
# Replace 192.168.1.14 with your server's actual IP address.
# Find your server IP on Windows: run `ipconfig` in PowerShell
# Find your server IP on Mac: System Settings → Wi-Fi → Details → IP Address
VITE_API_URL=http://192.168.1.14:8000
